recommend to reach this position.}) 8. Be3 d6 9. O-O O-O 10. c4 Nbc6 11. Nc3 e5
12. Rfd1 Be6 {I like this move - completing the development and connecting the
rooks.} 13. Nd5 {As we already know, the right reaction to the knight thrust
in the centre is to take more space on the queen side with the move a5!} a5 $1
14. a4 $6 {Black's strategy is to control the dark squares. The bishop on a7
